description.narrative: By 2023, national and sub-national authorities have strengthened capacity to plan, coordinate, and monitor inclusive, quality, child focused WASH services to communities and institutions (schools and health care facilities), including in emergencies., which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Disaster Risk Reduction, Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, underserved children equitably use safe water and practise safe sanitation and hygiene, including during humanitarian situations.

description.narrative: Despite, and as a result of, challenges resulting from the COVID-19 pandemic, progress has been made in WASH coordination, planning, financing, monitoring, institutional arrangements, and south-south cooperation, with increased use of virtual meetings and digital messaging app groups for coordination, planning, and information exchange, including between national and sub-national level.
